svg.text: The project list shows the name of all current viewed projects. Click on any project
name displayed to select it. The visualizations will adapt to your selection by
highlighting relevant areas in the different visualization tabs.
Use the filter tab to narrow down your search by Context
(faculty and course level), Project Details (project type,
project stage and year awarded) and Charting Param
Click on the table tab to obtain more detailed information about each
project, including enrollment cap and course location. The table
reflects selections that have been made using the Filters tab and the
Projects tab as well as any selections made within the visualization tabs.
In this project example, active learning through short activities (innovation) were
implemented to target lifelong learning skills as well as attitudes and motivation (impacts).
Observations (evaluation approach) were used to assess its effectiveness.
In the Innovation x Impact and Impact x Evaluation tabs, the color
intensity of the boxes shows the number of projects where there is and
intersection between an innovation and impact, or an impact and
evaluation. In this example, most projects use attitude surveys to evaluate

text.tspan: the effect of innovations on actions and behaviours or on attitudes and
